---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: "help_output(& [\"install\", \"--help\"])"
---
Install external software (r, quarto, uv, gh, rig, tinytex, duckdb)

Usage: hpds install [OPTIONS] <TOOL>

Arguments:
  <TOOL>  Tool to install (r, quarto, uv, gh, rig, tinytex, duckdb)

Options:
  -v, --verbose            Show more detail (underlying commands, tool names)
      --version <VERSION>  Install this exact version (only for tools that support pinning)
  -q, --quiet              Suppress all output except errors
  -y, --yes                Skip confirmation prompts; sudo steps still print what they will run
      --no-color           Disable colored output
      --config <PATH>      Use this config file instead of discovering hpds.toml
  -h, --help               Print help
